The paper deals with the problem of one-shot learning in computer vision, which is a subfield of computer science that falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a novel approach that utilizes a semantic concept space, which is a common technique in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also uses a neural network architecture called auto-encoder, which is a common technique in deep learning and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper deals with natural language processing and semantics, which is a subfield of computer science that falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL).
